7. The answer is no. Denote the five buckets, in some cyclic order, by $B_i$, $i = 0, \dots, 4$. Cinderella enforces that the following conditions are satisfied at the beginning of every round:

(a) Two adjacent buckets, say $B_1, B_2$ are empty;

(b) The buckets adjacent to the empty buckets in (a), i.e., $B_0, B_3$, have total content at most 1;

(c) the remaining bucket $B_4$ has content at most 1.

